svelte
<script>
  let count = 0;
  function increment() {
    count += 1;
  }
</script>

<button on:click={increment}>
  Clicked {count} {count === 1 ? 'time' : 'times'}
</button>
Svelte compiles this component directly to vanilla JavaScript at build-time, eliminating framework runtime overhead. The compiled output handles reactivity by generating efficient DOM updates when `count` changes, avoiding virtual DOM diffing. This results in smaller bundles (~50% smaller than React/Vue) and near-native performance.
